<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-421-126  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 421 126  OV: 08 420 886.andM; </DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  May 7 1990 v7 n18 p92(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Software Publishing Corp. PFS: First Publisher 3.0. (SoftwareReview) (one of seven evaluations of low-cost desktop publishingsoftware in 'Low-end packages offer publishing power.')andO;(evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Van Name, Mark L.; Catchings, Bill; Meads, Lori.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Software Publishing Corp's $149 PFS: First Publisher 3.0 is easyto use but lacks some important text-handling features.andP;  It doesnot offer automatic text flow between pages or automatichyphenation, but can place imported text on as many pages as arenecessary to hold it.andP;  The page view option is passive, and thetext-import facility supports a wide variety of word processorformats.andP;  Documentation is excellent and includes a 'Quick Tour'overview and context-sensitive on-line help.andP;  Buyers like FirstPublisher's ease of use and ability to change fonts on the fly.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Software Publishing Corp. (products).andO;Ticker:    SPCO.andO;Product:   PFS: First Publisher 3.0 (Desktop publishing software).andO;Topic:     Desktop PublishingSoftware PackagesEvaluation.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Software Publishing Corp.andM;PFS:FIRST PUBLISHER 3.0andM;PFS:First Publisher is generally strong and easy to use, but it omits someimportant features.andM;It includes a Layout Gallery of 21 different samples that can serve aspublication starting points.andP;  Users can also add up to five samples to thegallery.andM;Rather than paragraphs, the product uses &quot;baselines,&quot; which are like rulerswith formatting options, to control text.andP;  The baselines are necessary toperform all spacing functions, including indentation and centering.andM;PFS:First Publisher lacks two important text-handling features: automatichyphenation and automatic text flow between pages.andM;Both functions must be performed manually, but there is one exception: Whenimporting text, the product puts that text on as many pages as are necessaryto hold it.andM;There is a page view option, but it is, unfortunately, passive.andP;  As withExpress Publisher, PFS:First Publisher allows users to see, but not change,each page.andM;The product offers the best text-import options of the group, and itsgraphics-import features are also good.andP;  A &quot;snapshot&quot; facility lets userscapture screen images to files.andP;  There are also about 175 clip-art images.andP;  Aset of drawing tools lets users create and manipulate lines, boxes andcircles.andM;The product supports a large variety of printers.andP;  It includes two scalableBitstream fonts, and users can purchase additional Bitstream fonts.andP;  Userscan also create other font sizes with the included Bitstream FontWareprogram.andM;The documentation is among the best of the group.andP;  Its 320 pages include a&quot;Quick Tour,&quot; an overview of the program.andP;  There is also a context-sensitiveon-line Help facility.andM;Software Publishing Corp. of Mountain View, Calif., can be contacted at (415)962-8910.andM;----------Buyers say .andP;  .  .andM;Judge David Phares of Maricopa County in Phoenix, Ariz., uses First Publisheras a tool to help teach computer training classes at the National Center forState Courts.andM;&quot;I put together three-page training manuals, and even when the pages areblown up they still look good,&quot; he said.andM;Phares is impressed with the product's learning curve, citing Xerox's VenturaPublisher as much more difficult to use.andM;&quot;The commands make sense.andP;  You can change fonts on the fly,&quot; he said.andP;  Pharespraised the page preview function and column layout.andP;  &quot;It gives you a goodidea of where you're at and where you're going,&quot; he said.andM;Phares would like to see enhanced page capability in First Publisher's nextupgrade.andP;  &quot;I put out a nearly 30-page dictionary of computer terms forjudges, but right now, due to memory, the package can only handle nine or 10pages,&quot; he said.andM;&quot;I take the hacker's approach -- I like to see if I can get along withoutreading the manual, and [with First Publisher] I can,&quot; he said.andM;</TEXT></DOC>